	<string name="reference_costs">Road:\n1 lumber, 1 brick\n
		\nTown:\n1 lumber, 1
		wool, 1 grain, 1 brick\n
		\nCity:\n2 grain, 3 ore\n
		\nDevelopment
		card:\n1 wool, 1 grain, 1 ore</string>
	<string name="reference_build">Towns:
		\n- produce 1 resource when an adjacent tile
		is rolled
		\n- can build up to 5 towns
		\n- can\'t build beside another
		town or city
		\n- can only build where you have a road reaching
		\n- each
		town is worth 1 point\n
		\nCities:
		\n- produce 2 resources when an
		adjacent tile is rolled
		\n- replace a town
		\n- can build up to 4 cities
		\n- each city is worth 2 points\n
		\nRoads:
		\n- can build up to 15 roads
		\n- must build from a settlement or another road
		\n- the longest road
		is worth 2 points
		\n- minimum length for longest road is 5</string>
	<string name="reference_cards">Soldier cards:
		\n- most common development card
		\n-
		lets you move the robber
		\n- after moving robber, you steal from an
		adjacent player
		\n- no resources are produced from the tile where the
		robber resides\n
		\nProgress cards:
		\n- let you build 2 roads for free
		\n- road building rules still apply\n
		\nHarvest cards:
		\n- get 2 free resources\n
		\nMonopoly cards:
		\n- pick a resource type
		\n- steal all of this type from the other players\n
		\nVictory cards:
		\n- worth 1
		points
		\n- aren\'t shown to other players</string>

